Influenza viruses were detected in the 5.6–12% of cases, depending on the season, with the highest incidence corresponding to the H1N1 pandemic season (Fig. 1
). The proportion of different viruses detected is shown in Table 1
, being respiratory syncytial virus the most frequent. Following the current recommendations, 1477 children without influenza virus confirmed by laboratory, would had been treated with oseltamivir.
